    "body": "### Problem\n\n**Issue Description:**\r\nI am encountering an assertion failure in the libuv library when opening `.py` files in Neovim. The error message is as follows:\r\n\r\n```\r\n❯ nvim --headless init.py\r\nnvim: /__w/neovim/neovim/.deps/build/src/libuv/src/unix/core.c:301: uv__finish_close: Assertion `handle->flags & UV_HANDLE_CLOSING' failed.\r\n[1]    8598 IOT instruction  nvim --headless init.py\r\n```\r\n\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n\r\nThis issue occurs consistently and seems to be related to libuv.\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce:**\r\n1. Open Neovim with a specific `.py` file.\r\n2. Observe the assertion failure in libuv.\r\n\r\n**Environment Details:**\r\n- Neovim Version: `v0.9.5`\r\n- Operating System:  Ubuntu 22.04.4 LTS\r\n- libuv Version: 1.43.0-1\r\n\r\n**Additional Information:**\r\nIt does not seem related to my nvim configuration because using the --flag is causing the same issue:\r\n\r\n```\r\n❯ nvim --clean --headless init.py\r\nnvim: /__w/neovim/neovim/.deps/build/src/libuv/src/unix/core.c:301: uv__finish_close: Assertion `handle->flags & UV_HANDLE_CLOSING' failed.\r\n[1]    8824 IOT instruction  nvim --clean --headless init.py\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n\r\n**Expected Behavior:**\r\nNeovim should open `.py` files without encountering assertion failures in libuv.\r\n\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.5 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1692716794     system vimrc file: \"$VIM/sysinit.vim\"   fall-back for $VIM: \"/__w/neovim/neovim/build/nvim.AppDir/usr/share/nvim\"\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 22.04.4 LTS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nzsh 5.8.1 (x86_64-ubuntu-linux-gnu)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbob packet manager",
